                  <persName role="owner" corresp="PRS0000">The original donor is ʿƎqwǝba Giworgis mentioned in Additio 3 together with some of his family members. Also, their names are written in the supplications formulas over erasures, in the main hand (?): ʿƎqwǝba Giworgis (e.g., fols. 50vb, 59vb, 61ra, 62rb, 64vb, 65ra), his wife Mäḥarit/Mäḥarti Maryam (e.g., fols. 3rb, 59vb, 65ra), ʾAmḫa Giworgis (e.g., fols. 58ra, 71ra), Wäldä Giworgis (e.g., fols. 62rb, 70vb), Wälättä Maryam (e.g., fol. 64va).&#xD;
Later the Ms. was purchased by mämhǝre Gäbrä Wäld (s. Additio 2). At some point the name of another person, Gäbrä Mädḫǝn, was written interlineally above or below the supplication formulas on fols. 3rb, 50vb, 58ra, 78vb.&#xD;
According to Additio 3, the book was originally donated to the Church of Maryam Hǝrgwǝd (?).</persName>
